I had high expectations before going to this hotel and yet I return home with a bittersweet taste.
The lobby is beautiful, everything is very careful and it really seems that you are in the middle of a refuge in Yosemite. But nothing else, it's pretty and it's close to the park.
The rooms, which is what really matters, are very, very old.
-The beds make noise when you sit down, when you move when you sleep and it is very annoying. I also felt "strange" itching on my body.
-The furniture is very old and makes a lot of noise when opening and closing.
-old and dirty doors and the construction very badly done (very bad work touch-ups)
-The bathroom is very small and outdated.
-the wallpaper on the wall is falling off, the theming is really bad and careless.
-In the air duct, nobody ever cleaned it, there was a lot of dust and cobwebs.
-In six nights, no one has changed my bed sheets. They had a strange stain when I arrived at the hotel the first day and the same stain continued the following days of my entire stay. Not to waste my time in the park, I didn't go to the reception to make a claim, but this is too bad.
-They left me a bar of soap throughout my six-night stay and only on the day of return, they gave me shampoo for my hair.
-The bus service to the park is very slow, a bus passed every 15 minutes. I have also been to other hotels in Disneyland and there was a bus every 4 minutes.
-It's a bit annoying that whenever I entered the hotel they asked me to scan my Disney Loungefly backpack through the security tape and other people who passed by at the same time as me with larger backpacks did not ask them. They even asked me to scan the newly purchased Disney Christmas sealed train at the park.
The staff is not friendly at all.
I recommend this hotel when the following points have been improved:
1) Customer service and friendliness of the cast members.
2)renovation of the bedrooms completely (bathrooms, mattresses, beds, furniture and tv) and really create a good Disney theming (not a wallpaper that falls off the wall)
-faster bus service.
3) improve the presentation and cleanliness of the rooms.
As long as Disney does not change this I DO NOT RECOMMEND staying at this hotel. The lobby is beautiful but it is very uncomfortable to be in a dormitory in these poor conditions.
Much better even hotel Cheyenne. And if you want proximity to the parks, don't hesitate and go to New York. It is worth paying a little more and being in a clean, well-kept environment with friendly staff.

Check in was quick and easy and all staff I had dealings with were very pleasant and helpful. The shop has a good range of items (I got some pin badges that I had failed to find in the parks, and some snacks). I didn't use the pool or fitness centre this time, and did not visit the restaurant. When I visited in 2016 breakfast was included in the rate, but it did not seem good value to me to purchase on its own.
There was a long wait to drop off bags at the luggage room on the morning of check out, the queue was a bit disorganised and I would advise leaving extra time to account for this.
The main thing this hotel has going for it is the location, even from the furthest lodge it was very easy walking distance to the parks and Disney Village (and a pleasant walk by river and lake), I even found it close enough to come back to my room during the day if I needed a break or to change. Because of the good location and it being a Disney property, I suspect the needed modernisation and sprucing up will be slow to arrive, as they will continue to be fully booked regardless!

Extremely worn out three star property on the Disney Paris grounds. While the exterior and general theme are very well capturing the Pacific Northwest feel, the poor state of the rooms and facilities was shameful considering this three star hotel charges the same price as a five star in downtown Paris. The main attraction of staying here (or any other Disney hotel) is to benefit from complementary park tickets valid all days of your stay - including arrival and departure days - great value as unlikely you would purchase full price tickets for half days. We LOVE our visits to Disney but sadly the room at the Sequoia Lodge was quite disappointing, especially the bathroom. The shower leaked alllll over the bathroom floor, the shower head kept moving toward the wall, there was barely any soap (why not top it up a bit before each check in? We surely pay enough). The air conditioning in the room was completely ineffective so we slept without blankets and in light summer clothing. There was no tea/coffee in the room, or any bottled water (and Disney Village/Parks sell for ~â‚¬3.30 a bottle compared to ~â‚¬1 in Paris). Power outlets were in poorly thought out locations. No iron or fridge. All in all, the room was extremely dated, dark, and not worth the money spent at all :-((( It felt like a budget hotel?! On the plus side, the buffet was good enough to get started for the day and the location was quiet. The walk to the parks was great, we never needed the shuttle. We will hopefully be back at Disneyland Paris but won't choose Sequoia Lodge again. The Marvel Hotel would be my suggestion for location and modernity.

L'emplacement de l'hÃ´tel est a vendre. Pour le prix, c'est Ã  une minute Ã  pied du nouvel hÃ´tel Marvel, beaucoup plus cher, et situÃ© en bas de Disney Village. Visited between the 10th of July - 15th of July.
Hotel is very clean, well themed as are all Disney hotels. Staff very friendly at all times. The overall ambiance of the hotel is great and cannot complain.
The room we stayed in had a few issues that need addressing hence the three stars. There are two plug sockets in a room which can house four Adults. This is something to keep in mind if going friends or family as power banks are a necessity. Don't try and charge anything in the day though as staff will unplug all sockets when cleaning the room!
The decoration is good in the rooms and falls inline with the rest of the hotel theme. The main issue with this is it hasn't changed in about 20 years. Your not going to Disney for the 'cheaper' Hotels but it could use a lick of paint and some love. Our room also had issues regarding the plumbing as the sink wouldn't drain unless left for a few hours and the shower head would collapse onto you when in use. The shower was fixed in a timely fashion once notified but the sink was unchanged.
The location of the hotel is was sells it. For the price it is a minute walk from the new Marvel hotel, which is a lot more pricey, and is situated at the bottom of Disney Village. Its around 1Km walk from the hotel to the park which can be done in around 15-20 minutes as a slow walk. The price and location is brilliant. Its really appreciated after a full day in the park + fireworks and then walking back to the room.
If you are trying to save money but still want a full Disney experience i couldn't recommend another hotel more. Its abit rough around the edges compared to the higher priced options but does the job and still has that Disney feeling!

In the US this is a value resort at best, masquerading as a moderate, charging closer to deluxe. Staff was all great. Main lobby areas etc all quite nice. But the rooms - Golden Forest Club - are very dated with only ONE useful power outlet. One. Two only if you count the one literally one inch from the floor right by the front door. None near a bed. No way to charge a family full of electronics at all. The air conditioner is also useless and even set to its lowest temp does NOTHING to combat even 71 degree outside temperatures. The room felt like around 89 degrees and stuffy. Impossible to stay in or get much sleep even wearing next to nothing and no blankets. Windows canâ€™t be opened on top floor, either. Worst Disney room we have ever stayed in between Paris, Florida, and California. By far. Golden Forest Lounge is nice so at least there was that. Breakfast and tea time were both nice experiences. Further away from the actual parks than it looks, which is a long walk after a full day. I cannot at all recommended staying in this hotel until they do a very thorough room refurb, add useful power outlets by the beds, and put in A/C that actually does anything at all. People would die in this place if the heat got above 80 degrees outside. It is frankly a disgrace to Disney hotels and the Disney brand, but then again, so is Bob Chapek.

Zeer groot, sterk verouderd, maar toch echt een leuk hotel.
Wij zijn in dd mei vakantie naar Disneyland Parijs gegaan. We kozen om weer een keer in dit hotel te verblijven. The art of Marvel was beestachtig duur en New Port Bay hadden se al te vaak gezien.
De ambiance is en blijft. Leuk hier. Goed ontvangst en men doet hun best om je het nssr je zin te maken.
We vroegen om 3 kamers naast elkaar. Dat lukte niet. We kregen 2 naast elkaar en 1 op een andere verdieping. Dat vond de dame die ons hielp zelf niet netjes. Ze gaf ons alle info en spullen en stuurde ons naar het park. Rond 20.00 kon ik terugkomen en zouden ze kijken wat ze konden doen.
We kregen de 3e kamer niet echt in de buurt, maar het was wel op dezelfde verdieping. Ze hebben hun best gedaan.
Het hotel zelf is sterk verouderd. De lobby en eetgelegenheden waren m.i. wel goed op orde. De hallen waren echt aan een vernieuwing toe. De kamers ook wel, maar we kondr daar wel mee leven. We hadden een mooi uitzicht. Dat hielp ook.
Je kreeg een pasje met een saldo voor koffie,thee, warme choco. Ook was er een dispenser koud en bruisend water. Het zijn toch die kleine dingen die het doen.
Helaas was het zwembad dicht. Dat was voor ons wel een van de hoogtepunten van dit hotel.
Ontbijt was goed, maar je mket niet te laat komen. Je kan tot 11 uur ontbijten, maar na 10.15 kon je al geen koffie of thee meer halen en werd niet alles vers aangevuld. Toen we eerder gingen ontbijten was dit wel beter.
Al met al een prima plek om te verblijven, ondanks dat het een opknapbeurt nodig heeft.

Name: Hans Bcn
ReviewText:
(Traduit par Google) Evitez cet hÃ´tel Ã  tout prix. Nous avons sÃ©journÃ© dans une de leurs chambres en mars 2022. Nous nous attendions Ã  vivre une expÃ©rience magique dans un hÃ´tel de Disneyland, ayant la marque Disney comme gage de qualitÃ©. Loin des attentes, le systÃ¨me de chauffage central Ã©tait en panne et nous avons dormi 2 nuits dans des conditions glaciales. Nous avons parlÃ© au personnel de l'hÃ´tel qui a confirmÃ© avoir envoyÃ© quelqu'un pour l'examiner, mais le chauffage n'Ã©tait pas rÃ©parÃ© et aprÃ¨s s'Ãªtre plaint le deuxiÃ¨me soir, le gars de la rÃ©ception a mentionnÃ© qu'il enverrait un radiateur dans notre chambre. Le radiateur n'a jamais Ã©tÃ© livrÃ©. Nous avons dÃ» dormir avec nos vÃªtements, essayer de couvrir la couette avec nos manteaux (plus de couvertures dans la chambre), et cela n'a pas aidÃ© le lendemain Ã  nous rÃ©veiller tous les trois avec un rhume. Je comprends tout Ã  fait que la pandÃ©mie rend les choses plus complexes et que certaines entreprises de l'hÃ´tellerie sont en difficultÃ©. C'est bien, nous sommes tous humains et faisons des erreurs. Ma frustration ultime vient du service client de Disneyland Paris. Nous avons envoyÃ© 2 e-mails Ã  l'Ã©quipe centrale du service client, et j'ai reÃ§u une rÃ©ponse assez grossiÃ¨re m'informant que mon collÃ¨gue s'Ã©tait dÃ©jÃ  plaint et qu'ils ne rÃ©pondraient qu'Ã  lui. Pas une excuse, pas un seul "nous sommes dÃ©solÃ©s d'apprendre". 4 semaines plus tard, nous attendons toujours une rÃ©ponse. Nous avons chassÃ© leur service client, qui semble Ã©viter notre plainte. Il est inadmissible qu'une marque comme Disney gÃ¨re un service client d'une qualitÃ© aussi mÃ©diocre dans l'un de ses parcs. Certainement tuÃ© l'ambiance du 30e anniversaire, et il est peu probable que nous passions plus de vacances dans ce parc puisque j'ai Ã©galement eu une mauvaise expÃ©rience similaire avec le service client de Disneyland Paris en 2017. Nous choisirons Orlando Ã  l'avenir pour Ã©viter de telles mauvaises expÃ©riences client qui rendent votre vacances un cauchemar plein de frustration.
(Avis d'origine)
Avoid this hotel at all costs. We stayed in one of their rooms in March 2022. We were expecting a magical experience in a Disneyland hotel, having the Disney brand as a quality guarantee. Far from expectations, the central heating system was broken down and we slept 2 nights in freezing conditions. We spoke to the hotel staff who confirmed they had sent someone to look into it, but the heating was not fixed and after complaining on the second night, the guy at reception mentioned they would send a heater to our room. The heater was never delivered. We had to sleep with our clothes on, try to cover the duvet with our coats (no more blankets in the room), and this did not help for the next day to wake up the three of us with a cold. I totally understand the pandemic makes things more complex and certain companies in hospitality are struggling. This is fine, we are all humans and make mistakes. My ultimate frustation comes with the Disneyland Paris customer service. We have sent 2 emails to the central customer service team, and I received a pretty rude answer informing me my colleague had already complained and that they will respond only to him. Not an apologise, not a single â€œwe are sorry to hearâ€. 4 weeks later, we are still awaiting for an answer. We have chased their customer service, which seems to avoid our complaint. It is inadmissible for a brand like Disney to run such a low quality customer service in one of their parks. Definitely killed the 30th Anniversary vibe, and it is unlikely we will spend more holidays in this park since I had also a similar bad experience with Disneyland Paris customer service in 2017. We will choose Orlando moving forward to avoid such bad customer experiences that make your holidays a nightmare full of frustration.

Le troisiÃ¨me jour, j'ai remarquÃ© le matin que le bas de nos draps avait ce qu'il ressemblait Ã  des taches de sang, alors j'ai sorti les draps pour qu'ils soient Ã©vidents pour les femmes de mÃ©nage. InterrogÃ© sur un autre rÃ©ceptionniste pourquoi il y a encore des problÃ¨mes pour accÃ©der Ã  nos chambres et ils nous ont donnÃ© une explication diffÃ©rente que le systÃ¨me n'a pas changÃ© rÃ©cemment mais il pourrait y avoir des interfÃ©rences avec le magnÃ©tisme des cartes. Enfin dans notre chambre et j'ai rÃ©alisÃ© que les lits Ã©taient faits mais les draps n'Ã©taient pas changÃ©s, les taches Ã©taient juste cachÃ©es avec les couvre-lits. Bon essai! LittÃ©ralement tous les soirs au retour de nos belles journÃ©es dans les parcs, nous avons dÃ» courir Ã  la rÃ©ception pour pouvoir accÃ©der Ã  nos chambres. Je pense que c'est incroyable pour ce genre d'hÃ´tel d'avoir un tel manque de soutien et de compensation, surtout aprÃ¨s le montant d'argent que vous avez dÃ©pensÃ© dans leur Ã©tablissement. My family and I always used to go to the Sequoia Lodge during our holidays to Disneyland and haven't been there for a while. I was really excited to go back to this magical place with our kids and relatives. We unfortunately left the hotel after 4 days with a lot of disappointment. The first day we arrived, we couldn't have the third room we booked until 4 pm, which was no big deal as we already had the two other rooms. Although, when we came back that day around 7 pm to get our room, our magnetic cards weren't functioning so we went back to the reception to fix it. Went back up and the cards were still not working. We called them twice before someone finally showed up to let us in our room after almost an hour of wait. In one of the rooms, the heater was not working so someone had to come in and shut off the power. Second day, we came back in our rooms on the evening and the cards were not working again. Went to the reception and asked them for an explanation and they advised us of a change in their system. Third day, I noticed on the morning that the bottom of our bed sheets had what it looks like blood stains so I took the sheets out to be apparent for the cleaning ladies. Came back on the evening, our cards were not working AGAIN! Asked to another receptionist why there's still issues to access our rooms and they gave us a different explanation that the system did not change recently but there might be interference with the magnetism of the cards. Finally in our room and I realized that the beds were made but the sheets were not changed, the stains were just hidden with the bed covers. Good try! Fourth day and last evening at the hotel, we came back at night and guess what? The cards were once again not freaking working. Literally every night coming back from our nice days at the parks, we had to run to the reception to be able to access our rooms. I think it's unbelievable for this kind of hotel to have such a lack of support and compensation especially after the amount of money you spent in their establishment. I was strongly disappointed of their service and definitely not recommend or will go back to the Sequoia Lodge.

AprÃ¨s avoir parlÃ© Ã  quelques personnes du concierge, qui Ã©taient adorables mais n'ont pas offert une tonne d'aide, je me sentais dÃ©sespÃ©rÃ©e. Je suis retournÃ© voir le Concierge aprÃ¨s Ãªtre allÃ© Ã  la gare qui m'a simplement remis un dÃ©pliant, qui bien sÃ»r Ã©tait en franÃ§ais. Maintenant, j'Ã©tais complÃ¨tement impuissant parce que je ne pouvais pas le lire. Je l'ai apportÃ© au Sequoia Lodge et l'ai montrÃ© Ã  Lorena, totalement sur le point de fondre en larmes, et elle a rapidement pris la brochure et s'est donnÃ© pour MISSION de m'aider. Elle a appelÃ© et attendu en attente et a appelÃ© et parlÃ© Ã  des gens plusieurs fois pour moi pendant notre sÃ©jour (qui n'a durÃ© que deux jours et une nuit.) Elle s'est mÃªme assurÃ©e que ses collÃ¨gues connaissaient ma situation et les ont fait m'aider quand elle Ã©tait partie pour le jour/en pause. Nous n'avons jamais rÃ©cupÃ©rÃ© mon sac, mais cela n'a pas vraiment d'importance car je ne peux pas en dire assez sur Lorena. Ange absolu !
(Avis d'origine)
Lorena at the Sequoia Lodge Concierge helped me SO MUCH! I lost a bag on the TGV train that took us from the airport to the station that connects to Disneyland. After speaking to a few people at the Concierge, who were lovely but didn't offer a ton of help, I felt hopeless. I went back to the Concierge after going to the train station who simply handed me a pamphlet, which of course was in French. Now I was completely helpless cause I couldn't read it. I took it to the Sequoia Lodge and showed it to Lorena, totally about to burst into tears, and she quickly took the pamphlet and made it her MISSION to help me. She called and waited on hold and called and spoke to people multiple times for me during our stay (which was only two days and one night.) She even made sure her colleagues knew my situation and had them assist me when she was off for the day/on breaks. We never did get my bag back, but it doesn't really matter because I cannot say enough about Lorena. Absolute angel!

-Il dispose d'un coin salon-bar pour le cafÃ© ou les cocktails. Ils ont Ã©galement jouÃ© Ã  des matchs de sport en direct ici aussi

- La chambre n'avait que 3 prises de courant - dont 1 ne fonctionnait pas. Aucun n'Ã©tait prÃ¨s des lits non plus. Je prendrais une prolongation la prochaine fois
- Nous n'avons pas pu utiliser la baignoire car la baignoire n'avait pas de prise ... la salle de bain pourrait peut-Ãªtre Ãªtre rÃ©novÃ©e, le bois autour de la baignoire Ã©tait cassÃ© et la pomme de douche Ã©tait presque cassÃ©e.
- La piscine Ã©tait glaciale, nous n'avons passÃ© que 10 minutes dans la piscine. La diapositive Ã©tait vraiment cool. J'imagine que les enfants adoreraient vraiment cette rÃ©gion
- Pas de plateau / bouilloire dans la chambre. Chaque personne reÃ§oit une boisson chaude gratuite d'un distributeur automatique. Ce distributeur automatique n'Ã©tait pas dans notre quartier et les boissons n'Ã©taient pas trÃ¨s bonnes non plus.

Spent 5 nights here Sept 2019. There are many pros and a few cons to this hotel.
Pros
-Location is amazing, a couple of minutes walk from Disney Villiage and from there a few more minutes to the theme parks. We mostly walked, as it took around 7-10mins from our room to the front gates of the theme parks. If it was raining we got the shuttle bus. Running every 15 minute from the hotel lobby.
-The room was large in size with plenty of storage for clothing
-Atmosphere, we loved the hotel and the vibes it gave. It seemed very safe and secure and the staff are very pleasant.
-It has a lounge bar area for coffee or cocktails. They also played live sports games here too
-It has a restaurant (we never used) and pool/gym facilities.
Con
- The room only had 3 plug outlets - 1 of which didn't work. None were by the beds either. I'd take an extension lead next time
- We couldn't use the bath as the tub didn't have a plug... the bath area could maybe use a revamp, the wood around the tub was broke and the shower head was nearly broke.
- The pool area was freezing, we only spent 10 minutes in the pool. The slide was really cool. I'd imagine children would really love this area
- No in room tea/coffee facilities. Each person is credited one free hot drink from a vending machine. This vending machine wasn't in our block plus the drinks weren't very nice either.
Overall, I would stay again at Sequoia Lodge, it's a very peaceful and relaxing hotel, in a brilliant and convenient location.
